      cons={["Requires separate kettle and workflow steps.", "No built-in milk steaming."]}
    />
    <p><strong>Key specs:</strong> Manual lever · user-controlled pressure · pressurized/non-pressurized options · no milk system · Espresso-capable: Yes.</p>
    <p><strong>Retention/static note:</strong> Requires quality grinding; dose consistency and static control from your grinder have direct impact on shot quality.</p>
    <p><strong>Why it wins this slot:</strong> It offers the best espresso ceiling under $200 for users willing to trade convenience for control.</p>

    <h3>6) Nespresso Essenza Mini — Best Pod Convenience Under $200</h3>
    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Best for users who want consistent coffee-fast workflow and minimal cleanup rather than true espresso craft.</p>
    <p><strong>Buy this if...</strong> speed, tiny footprint, and no dial-in learning curve matter most.</p>
    <p><strong>Skip this if...</strong> you want fresh-ground espresso or milk-texture control.</p>
