      cons={["Capsule ecosystem locks you into pods.", "Flavor ceiling is below fresh-ground pump espresso."]}
    />
    <p><strong>Key specs:</strong> Pod machine · 19-bar claim · pod chamber · no milk system · 20.3 oz tank · Espresso-capable: No.</p>
    <p><strong>Retention/static note:</strong> Not grinder-based; pod freshness and capsule age replace grinder retention concerns.</p>
    <p><strong>Why it wins this slot:</strong> It is still the fastest low-effort way to get espresso-style drinks in this price range.</p>

    <h3>7) De'Longhi ECP3420 — Best Long-Term Budget Durability</h3>
    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Best for buyers who want a proven model with stable daily reliability and serviceable parts.</p>
    <p><strong>Buy this if...</strong> you want a safer long-term ownership bet over feature-heavy newcomers.</p>
    <p><strong>Skip this if...</strong> you need maximum milk automation or modern one-touch workflows.</p>
    <ProsCons
      pros={["Proven reliability track record in budget category.", "Manual steam wand gives useful milk control with practice.", "Good parts support and accessory compatibility."]}
      cons={["Design feels dated versus newer compact models.", "Still relies on pressurized basket defaults out of box."]}
